<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-12-29T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-12-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="366" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d366">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3463: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Nicholson</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-12-29T15:00:00-04:00">December 29, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 5:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Paraguay has agreed to extension of the armistice for 8 days. Repeated to
                            La Paz, Montevideo, and Buenos Aires.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Nicholson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>